connect

public void connect(android.app.Activity activity)
Connects to facebook granting only basic permissions. connectCallback(int, int, Intent) must be called on the Activity.onActivityResult(int, int, Intent) to complete login.

Parameters:
activity - The Activity where the authorization dialog will be shown.

connectCallback

public String connectCallback(int requestCode,
                              int resultCode,
                              android.content.Intent data)
IMPORTANT: This method must be invoked at the top of the calling activity's onActivityResult() function or Facebook authentication will not function properly! If you're connecting from a fragment, you should call the fragment's Fragment.onActivityResult(int, int, Intent) manually from your activity.

Parameters:
requestCode - The request code for the Activity.onActivityResult(int, int, Intent).
resultCode - The result code obtained on Activity.onActivityResult(int, int, Intent).
data - The data intent obtained on Activity.onActivityResult(int, int, Intent).
Returns:
The access token required to connect to Facebook.
